confirmed_gaps.remediation:
Add to tofu/opconnect/outputs.tf (opconnect is where tls_private_key.ansible lives — cleanest, no extra 1P read):

output "ansible_ssh_key_fingerprint" {
  description = "SHA256 fingerprint of the Ansible SSH key (for reference/debugging)."
  value       = tls_private_key.ansible.public_key_fingerprint_sha256
}

Not sensitive (a fingerprint, like the sibling public-key output). Alternatively, to mirror the compute-side public-key output, add it to tofu/compute/outputs.tf by extracting the existing 1Password field: in compute/ssh-keys.tf locals add a select for f.label == "public_key_fingerprint_sha256" (the field is already written by opconnect's op-write-ssh-key.sh:80), then output it from compute. opconnect placement is preferred — it's the source of truth and avoids depending on the 1P data read. Low priority: cosmetic; the value is already durable in 1Password.
